The paper is about information retrieval (IR) and neural ranking models, which are commonly studied in the sub-field of IR (cs.IR). The use of axioms to guide the search for better relevance estimation functions is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions modifying documents, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and computer vision (cs.CV). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR, followed by cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.AI, and cs.CV.
